📝 Next Steps:

1. Update environment variables:
   az vm run-command invoke --resource-group DSC-TEAM --name coder-vm \
     --command-id RunShellScript \
     --scripts 'cd ~/suna-production && nano suna/backend/.env'

2. Restart services after updating credentials:
   az vm run-command invoke --resource-group DSC-TEAM --name coder-vm \
     --command-id RunShellScript \
     --scripts 'cd ~/suna-production && docker compose -f docker-compose.production.yml restart'

3. Initialize GraphDB:
   az vm run-command invoke --resource-group DSC-TEAM --name coder-vm \
     --command-id RunShellScript \
     --scripts 'curl -X POST http://localhost:7200/rest/repositories -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d "{\"id\":\"carbonbim-thailand\",\"title\":\"SUNA\",\"ruleset\":\"rdfsplus-optimized\"}"'

4. Setup Cloudflare domain (see setup-cloudflare-domain.sh)

